The Social Democratic Party (SDP) governorship candidate in Adamawa State, Dr Umar Ardo, has vowed to concede defeat to Senator Aishatu Dahiru Binani, the governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), if she defeats him in Yola South, her LG of origin, in the forthcoming election. In a statement, Tuesday, Ardo said the people of Adamawa can no longer be deceived into voting based on enticement with “proceeds of corruption.” He said, “I said it before on national TV, and I am repeating it. If Sen. Binani wins her local government, Yola South, against me, l will concede defeat and let her be sworn in as governor.” 